Database Size

For 500 Windows systems:

Assets: ~500 rows
Evidence: 20,000–30,000 rows (assuming ~40–60 checks per asset)
Vulnerabilities: 2,000–10,000 rows depending on scan results
Scan History: ~180,000 rows over a year if retained
Framework Mappings: ~1,000 rows
Controls: ~2,000–3,000 rows

SQLite handles this comfortably; the database would typically remain under 500 MB.

Architectural Recommendation

Instead of Windows Task Scheduler invoking different scripts, every scheduled task would call the same entry point with a job name.

Invoke-SentinelGRC.ps1 -Job Inventory
Invoke-SentinelGRC.ps1 -Job Compliance
Invoke-SentinelGRC.ps1 -Job ImportNessus
Invoke-SentinelGRC.ps1 -Job WeeklyReports

Internally, the framework would resolve the job to the appropriate modules, manage execution order, prevent overlapping runs, record execution in ScanHistory, and produce a single consolidated log. This reduces operational complexity, makes scheduling easier, and allows new capabilities to be added by registering new jobs rather than creating additional scheduled tasks.
